@startuml ReturnBook
title Activity Diagram: Return Book

' Description:
' This activity diagram describes the process of returning a borrowed book.
' Steps:
' 1. Member presents the book for return.
' 2. System looks up the loan record associated with the book and member.
' 3. System checks whether the return date is past the due date.
' 4. If overdue, system calculates the fine amount based on days overdue.
' 5. System creates a fine record and notifies the member of the fine owed.
' 6. If on time, no fine is generated.
' 7. System marks the loan record as returned and records the return date.
' 8. System increments the available copy count of the book.
' 9. System confirms the successful return to the member.
' 10. Activity ends.

|Member|
start
:Present Book for Return;
|System|
:Look Up Loan Record;
:Check Return Date vs Due Date;
if (Overdue?) then (yes)
  :Calculate Fine Amount;
  :Create Fine Record;
  :Notify Member of Fine;
  |Member|
  :Acknowledge Fine;
  |System|
else (no (on time))
endif
:Mark Loan as Returned;
:Update Book Copy Count (+1);
:Confirm Return to Member;
|Member|
:Receive Return Confirmation;
stop
@enduml
